briefdescription.para: Reusable set of declarative rules and If/Then constructs. The set may be reused in several places in the FormDesign model. Each rule runs an expression to return a Boolean value, and runs or implies an action dependant on the Boolean result.

detaileddescription.para: Some rules (e.g., IllegalSelectionTest, IllegalSelectionSets) do not run an explicit action, instead leaving the resulting action up to the form implementation. For example, when an illegal combination of ListItms are selected, the implementaion may elect to undo the last ListItem selection, and/or pop up a warning message, and/or flag the illegaly paired items with a background color or error icon, etc.
